HEADWORD: Isocryme
<hw>I"so*cryme</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> +
Gr. <?/ cold.]</ety> <fld>(Phys. Geog.)</fld> <def>A line connecting
points on the earth's surface having the same mean temperature in the
coldest month of the year.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isocrymic</ent>⟦br⟧
